pullRequest.body:
`surjective_quot_mk` => `Quot.mk_surjective`
`surjective_quotient_mk` => `Quotient.mk_surjective`
`surjective_quotient_mk'` => `Quotient.mk'_surjective`
`Quotient.surjective_Quotient_mk''` => `Quotient.mk''_surjective`


This is consistent with the naming of most lemmas about `Function.Surjective` in mathlib.

Also make `Setoid` parameters implicit.

---

Many lemmas in Mathlib use `*_surjective` instead of `surjective_*`.
Have we decided which one should be used?
Please update the PR description to match the new names
The PR description has already been updated.

It's interesting that we have https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/naming.html#injectivity but no corresponding rule for naming things `mk_surjective` instead of `surjective_mk`. It might be worth running a quick zulip poll to see if there's consensus.

It's interesting that we have https://leanprover-community.github.io/contribute/naming.html#injectivity but no corresponding rule for naming things `mk_surjective` instead of `surjective_mk`. It might be worth running a quick zulip poll to see if there's consensus.
Arguably you should use `deprecated alias` for these, which also adjusts the docstring. Maybe it's not worth the risk of changing the statement by accident though.

pullRequest.title: chore(Data/Quot): rename `surjective_*_mk` => `*.mk_surjective`
